{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Guide Falls | photo = Guide_Falls_2.jpg | photo_width = | photo_caption = Guide Falls, in summer 2007. | map = Tasmania | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|41|09|00|S|145|48|00|E|region:AU-TAS_type:waterbody_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref name=ga1>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Guide Falls (TAS)|feature=TAS06319}}</ref><ref name=ga2>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Upper Guide Falls (TAS)|feature=TAS14078}}</ref> | location = [[North West Tasmania|North West]] [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]]<ref name= thinktasmania>{{cite journal |title=Guide Falls reserve, Ridgley: Must do!|url=http://www.think-tasmania.com/guide-falls-reserve-ridgley-must-do/|journal=think-tasmania.com|date = 15 February 2013}}</ref> | type = [[Waterfall#Types|Tiered{{endash}}cascade]] | elevation = {{convert|187|m}}<ref name=bonzle/> {{AHD}} | height = {{convert|22|-|38|m}}<ref name=bonzle>{{cite web|url=http://www.bonzle.com/c/a?a=p&p=253897&cmd=sp|title=Map of Guide Falls, TAS|work=Bonzle Digital Atlas of Australia|date=|accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref> | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = Guide River | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Guide Falls''' and '''Upper Guide Falls''', a [[Waterfall#Types|tiered{{endash}}cascade waterfall]] on the Guide River, is located in the [[North West Tasmania|North West]] region of [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]].<ref name= thinktasmania/>
==Location and features== The waterfalls are situated about 19km south of {{TAScity|Burnie}}<ref>{{cite journal |title=Guide falls|url=http://www.discoverburnie.net/what-to-see/guide-falls.html|journal=discoverburnie.net}}</ref> at an elevation of {{convert|187|m}} [[Australian Height Datum|above sea level]] and descend in the range of {{convert|22|-|38|m}}.<ref name=bonzle/>
To access the falls from Burnie, take the road towards [[Cradle Mountain]], and then turn right just outside the boundary of Ridgley and continue down into the gully and turn left at a posted gate sign. Once entered, the Guide River is to the right and continue to drive up the gravel road where the falls are located. The top is safe and there are great view from the fenced lookout. There is also a set of steps that lead down to the bottom of the falls. Around the vicinity there are also picnic tables and barbecue areas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-guide-falls.html|title=Guide Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|publisher=Johnny T. Cheng|date=27 November 2006|accessdate=31 May 2014}}</ref>
