'''Hillier Moss''' ({{coord|60|43|S|45|36|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a wet, level, low-lying area, which has several small pools and extensive moss carpets, located {{convert|0.2|nmi|km|1}} north of [[Lenton Point]] in southeastern [[Signy Island]], Antarctica. It was named by the [[UK Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] after [[Edward R. Hillier]], a [[British Antarctic Survey]] medical officer and leader at [[Signy Research Station]], 1967.<ref name=gnis/>

