'''Khoroolol''' ({{lang-mn|хороолол|horoolol}}) is the [[Mongolia]]n equivalent for ''neighbourhood'' or, in densely built residential areas ([[Quarter (urban subdivision)|quarter]]), for the [[Russian language|Russian]] ''[[mikrorayon]]''. In [[Ulaanbaatar]], the apartment khoroolols built during socialist times carry numbers between one and nineteen, though some are named after higher numbers like 40,000 and 120,000.<ref>[http://dspace.num.edu.mn/bitstream/123456789/144/1/Chinbat_2.pdf Chinbat Badamdorj , ''Changes in the Internal Structure of Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia''], p.4f</ref>
