'''Mount Wuteve''' is a [[mountain]] located in [[Liberia]], whose summit is the [[elevation|highest point]] in [[Liberia]]. It is located in the [[Guinea Highlands]] [[mountain range|range]], whose parent range is the [[West Africa Mountains]]. Data from the [[Shuttle Radar Topography Mission]] reveals that the correct elevation of its summit is 1,440 meters, and not the previously quoted 1,380 meters.<ref>{{cite web|title=ViewfinderPanorama.org|url=http://www.viewfinderpanoramas.org/elevmisquotes.html#africa|last=de Ferranti|first=Jonathan|date=28 June 2014}}</ref> It is also known as Mount Wologizi among locals of the Loma tribe.
